{"$ambrosia":"aero:interactive:9417ac60-5f60-11ea-8e69-affb2224d7e8:*","$id":"067557f0-44e0-11ed-887c-b85f9fbdfc63","$workspaceId":"7fff47c0-44d6-11ed-bcef-d5307f42495c","$projectId":"86cb0040-44df-11ed-8442-dbcbc27803ca","annotations":[],"configSchemaVersion":"/pluginGenericSchema/v1","config":{"stage":{"sections":[{"rows":[{"columns":[{"stageElements":[{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"heading-two","ref":"7c822700-48a4-4f03-b2e8-d8c58bfb28c0","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Exiting an Investment in a Private Company","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"d21fd2c5-fd3f-452e-ba81-14b318a9dee3"},{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"7685059f-2cc7-4bde-8f1f-5e0c3780ad53","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Like any relationship, the one between a firm and its investors is subject to change as needs and resources develop. An important consideration for investors in private companies is their ","marks":[]},{"data":{"ref":"cf2ff116-edbe-43eb-b82c-915f423f65c8","stage":{"ref":"4cc5dfdb-f48c-40d6-9212-34e59639d894","sections":[{"ref":"4cef5150-cbf3-46d2-ae15-d672d2783a3c","rows":[{"ref":"ad468165-0970-4004-846a-d3d505fe360a","columns":[{"ref":"fab42704-33b7-4034-9b82-5fbb41971a72","stageElements":[{"ref":"6464fef4-08ab-4757-b0ac-465d700ffe98","type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"button","ref":"54e22d20-5970-4f60-8e7b-0c237628e5ba","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"73822703-0bf0-4fde-942f-2f8d3b03d50c","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"An important consideration for investors in private companies, it details how they will eventually realize the return from their investment.","marks":[]}],"data":{}}],"data":{}}]}}}]}]}]}]}},"nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"exit strategy","marks":[]}],"object":"inline","type":"key-term","ref":"fe0218c0-b313-4c5c-a429-198594166db6"},{"object":"text","text":"—how they will eventually realize the return from their investment. Investors exit in two main ways: through an acquisition or through a public offering. Often, large corporations purchase successful start-up companies. In such a case, the acquiring company purchases the outstanding stock of the private company, allowing all investors to cash out. Roughly 76% of venture capital exits from 2014–2018 occurred through mergers or acquisitions with typical deal sizes in the range of $80 million to $100 million.","marks":[]},{"data":{"ref":"ca6027a2-2654-4c2a-b512-bbef999c8df9","stage":{"ref":"febc2a20-6885-412b-98ae-ba2636deb65c","sections":[{"ref":"f3190eaf-a5f0-4759-a4bf-5fdbe4b186d6","rows":[{"ref":"0eabc462-f906-4589-bb0a-254bd39a7b85","columns":[{"ref":"a8ded0a1-27ae-4115-bbe0-a2b839699b0f","stageElements":[{"ref":"eda82a4d-2172-4d69-a3fd-dfebb5a7a7a1","type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"button","ref":"1600d92f-ee99-4bd4-9bec-804af15cde82","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"a449ee94-05fe-4861-863f-01f37242ea9c","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"The National Venture Capital Association.","marks":[]}],"data":{}}],"data":{}}]}}}]}]}]}]}},"nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"5","marks":[]}],"object":"inline","type":"footnote","ref":"90012a0f-b41a-4719-aafa-669fd5eb881a"},{"object":"text","text":" The alternative way for the company to allow its investors to liquidate their investment is to become a publicly traded company.","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"d19ba19a-d353-4d96-9c33-7d7ae72366c6"},{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"a1aee5a4-9f5d-4af4-889e-39a72294ed41","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Over time, the value of a share of Facebook’s stock and the size of its funding rounds increased. Because Goldman Sachs and its investors were willing to pay $1.5 billion for just 3% of the company in January 2011, the valuation of existing stock had increased significantly, representing a substantial capital gain for early investors. Because Facebook was still a private company, however, investors could not realize this gain by selling their stock in the public stock markets. In the next section, we discuss the process a firm goes through to sell shares to the public and have its shares traded on a public market.","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"4033818e-98ea-4cac-8b5d-da96f5db1723"}]}]}]},{"cssClass":"aside-group Sidebar_1Aside","rows":[{"columns":[{"stageElements":[{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"heading-two","ref":"df678840-f003-4f48-a120-7d3c83bbe5bd","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Concept Check","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"8d4f773d-e670-42c8-8859-863ce469953a"},{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"ordered-list","data":{"listOptionType":"1","startValue":1},"ref":"02bd31df-4425-4831-ad4c-87546e0475dd","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"7097d7de-6d39-41e9-b526-9c191dc4e6f1","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"4e481b94-629b-4cb2-8b5d-637f3fad7a8c","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"What are the main sources of funding for private companies to raise outside equity capital?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]},{"object":"block","type":"list-item","data":{"direction":"auto"},"ref":"1508a3a9-b19e-45a3-8e31-8884d781b7c8","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"cc46474e-ca5d-401f-b527-a7e682363b47","nodes":[{"object":"text","